The implementation of author search (using bi-grams) means that if a user entered "Jeff L" the L part of his surname will not be considered in the search and he'll get a whole bunch of Jeff's back with no restriction on the surname.

This has been documented at http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Copy+of+Searching+Confluence however it is a shame to be discarding that useful bit of filtering the user has entered.

